<br>
no, not pain.<br>
<br>
PAIN!!<br>
<br>
Agony!  Excruciating, palpitating, throbbing, grinding PAIN!!<br>
<br>
He lived.  How, he had no clue, but he lived.  Faces swam around him, a dark voice whispered...  my lord, help me, your servant, your child... I?  Help another?  Impossible!  ...my lord, please, you know i live only to serve... Impossible i say!  Show yourself, Phantom!<br>
<br>
  At those words, the shadows seemed to coalesce.. a vision he saw, which could not be true... there, lying on the grass next to another body, that of the dead elven bitch!  He gasped, shocked, as he realized that body was his!! <br>
<br>
How is this possible?  How can this be?  The form on the ground stirred slightly... it... HE... was still breathing, albeit slightly.  The phantom voice rang in his head.  ...Lord, please...  It was coming from... the body!  HIS body!!  <br>
<br>
YOU SEE, LITTLE ONE, HOW IMPERFECT AND FRAGILE YOUR EXISTENCE IS TO ONE SUCH AS MYSELF<br>
<br>
My lord?<br>
<br>
YET SOMEHOW YOU THINK TO CALL ME FATHER<br>
THIS AMUSES ME NO END<br>
<br>
My Lord Innoruuk!<br>
<br>
SOME CHOOSE TO NAME ME SUCH<br>
MORE AMUSEMENT FOR ME, I AM ABOVE SUCH NAMING<br>
<br>
Great Lord... what has happened?  Why am i here?<br>
<br>
YOU DO NOT PAY VERY MUCH ATTENTION, MORTAL<br>
<br>
YOU AMUSE ME<br>
<br>
IF I CHOSE YOU WOULD NOW GO TO THE AFTERLIFE...  AND I DO NOT THINK THAT YOU WOULD APPRECIATE WHAT YOU FOUND THERE<br>
<br>
BUT THE AMUSEMENT SUFFICES... YOU BRING DEATH TO THE LIGHT, AND USE THE POWERS I GAVE YOU WISELY<br>
<br>
The darkness coalesced upon the hapless knight once more, and when he awoke, he was standing near the entrance to Neriak, wearing only light clothing.  His.. body?  was in the eastern commonlands, near the ridge between Nektulos forest and Freeport.  It didn't take him long at all to get there, although when he did, he got many strange looks from people.  He didn't understand at first, but then he realized they were seeing a dark elf strip a corpse that looked just like himself, and then putting on the plate armor like it was custom fitted for him.<br>
<br>
As he did, he heard that fearsome voice once more, now only a whisper<br>
<br>
go, my son, go forth and kill, that i may have my revenge upon the gods of light<br>
<br>
i have granted you new powers as well, use them as wisely as you have the ones you already had<br>
<br>
He chuckled to himself... amusement for the Lord?  If that was what the Father wanted from him, then he would give it.  Elves...  Humans... even the diminuitive ones.  They would feel his wrath for his Lord's amusement.  He tried to be a good son.<br>
<br>
He stood, and looked to the night sky.  It was a perfect night to sacrifice to his Lord.  He ran swiftly into the near distance, seeking a new victim.<br>
<br>
In the distance, a cry of pain, and even further away, phantom laughter...<br>
<br>
